title: For Sale/Trade:  Stoeger Vursan model 2000 max 4 camo 12 guage
postcontent:
This is the ultimate Turkey/Duck gun. Stoeger's Vursan shotguns are manufactured by the BERETTA Group. 

The Vursan Model 2000 is the only shotgun licenced to use the Benelli inertia-recoil operating system - the heart of the world's most prestigious and expensive Semi Autos. 

Unlike common gas-operated guns whose fore-ends conceal operating rods, pistons, O-rings, valves and other moving parts, the inertia system is entirely contained inside the receiver. The results? A trimmer fore-end, better balance, more reliable operation and the ability to fire everything from light target ammunition to the heaviest waterfowl loads without adjustments. And because propellant gas isn't used to cycle the action, inertia guns like the Model 2000 stay cleaner, even after hundreds of shots. Even in the toughest conditions, your new Model 2000 will keep on firing! 

The Vursan is also capable of taking up to 5 rounds standard without a magazine extension.

I've recently stepped up to a Kimber and so this gun is now available to someone new. This is a quality little pistol that will serve you well for years to come. It disassembles exactly like a Glock...in fact, this is almost like the micro that Glock never made.

Superb accuracy, extremely concealable, and excellent ergonomics make this an excellent choice for a concealed carry even in light summer clothing. Sure, you could conceal a Glock 26 easily in the cooler months, but it becomes much trickier in shorts and a tee shirt. This pistol will give you piece of mind all 4 seasons.

A micro-compact .380 automatic pistol made entirely in the USA. Designed with safety in mind, the DB380 features a "ZERO-Energy" striker firing system with a mechanical firing pin block, a steel magazine catch to secure a sheet metal magazine and real windage-adjustable sights, all in a lightweight pistol.

 A steel trigger (not plastic like so many others) with dual connecting bars allows for a crisp smooth, trigger pull. The DB380 features a FEA (Finite Element Analysis) designed slide and barrel that is stronger than any comparable firearm, resulting in durability with less felt recoil, and the absence of removable pins or tools makes field stripping easier than ever. The slide, barrel, and internal parts are coated to resist corrosion, making this pistol a lifetime investment.

title: For Sale:  Rare Like New Ruger Police Carbine .40  S&W cal
postcontent:
The Ruger Police Carbine is a pistol caliber carbine designed as a companion to the Ruger P Series pistols. As of 2007, Ruger has discontinued production citing low demand. It is a semi-automatic carbine using a blowback action. The Carbine uses the same ammunition and magazines as the Ruger P Series 9mm and .40 S&W caliber pistols.

Both the PC9 (the 9mm version) and the PC4 (.40 S&W) are patterned after the highly successful Ruger 10/22 carbine. The Carbine is intended as a shoulder weapon for police use, although it is available for sale to civilians as well. The intent is that an officer will carry a Ruger P Series pistol as a sidearm, and keep a Carbine available (for example, in his/her patrol vehicle) as a shoulder weapon if needed. Since the carbine has a 16-inch (410 mm) barrel, it provides more power with the same ammunition used by the 4-inch (100 mm) barreled pistol The carbine also provides additional accuracy and range over the pistol.
